President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 22, 2012, as National Hunting and Fishing Day in the United States. The proclamation recognizes the important role that America's great outdoors play in the nation's life and celebrates the legacy of conservation. It acknowledges the efforts of hunters and anglers in protecting and preserving the lands and waters they cherish. The proclamation also highlights the 75th anniversary of the Federal Aid in Wildlife Restoration Act, which provided funding for habitat conservation. President Obama emphasizes the need for grassroots-level involvement and partnerships with states, communities, and nonprofits to ensure effective environmental stewardship. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities.